			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">A lot of threading tests that are flaky on Windows have a common failure mode: they return with exit status -1.  This seems to indicate that they have the same cause.

The failures occur with both newlib and glibc.

Here is a list of failures I've seen with exit status -1:

nacl_glibc.run_thread_stack_alloc_test, xp-glibc-opt
nacl_glibc.run_cond_wait_test, win7-32-bare-glibc-opt
nacl_glibc.run_egyptian_cotton_test, xp-glibc-opt
nacl_glibc.run_egyptian_cotton_test, win7-64-bare-glibc-opt
nacl_newlib.run_types_srpc_test_nexe, vista-64-newlib-opt
nacl_newlib.run_thread_stack_test_irt, windows 7 64-bit
nacl_newlib.run_second_tls_test, win7-64-bare-newlib-opt
